From 5d8643eb5731ba2dc9901f00782effc13b92ac44 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jernej Skrabec <jernej.skrabec@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 09:51:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 08/20] media: cedrus: Add VC-1 decoding support

Add a stateless VC-1 / WMV3 decoder for the Cedrus VPU, driven by the
V4L2 VC-1 slice parameters and bitplane controls. It supports the Simple,
Main and Advanced profiles in progressive, interlaced-frame and
interlaced-field modes, covering all picture types (I, P, B, BI and
skipped), the variable quantizer and transform modes, intensity
compensation, range reduction, overlap smoothing and the seven bitplane
types.

The register programming was verified against the Allwinner vendor
libraries (the libawwmv3 binary and the CedarX libve sources): the MVMODE
translation, B-fraction scaling, FRFD/BRFD derivation, the per-field
intensity-compensation backup state, the VOP DQUANT parameters and the
picture/interlace control fields all match the vendor behaviour.

Streams the hardware cannot handle are rejected during control
validation: the Complex profile, reduced-resolution (RESPIC) coding and
out-of-range PQINDEX values.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
